    <h2>Concepts</h2>
    <p>The central concepts specific for this research line will be measured as follows:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Structural variables: absolute and relative group sizes and the degree of diversity.</li>
      <li>Cultural variables: for the perceived social distances and ethnic-cultural boundaries, we rely on self-reporting in surveys.</li>
      <li>In-group, organizational and generalized trust.</li>
      <li>Power of a group within an organization can be measured through power-related variables, such as number of employees among senior staff, number of formal representatives (e.g. elected union representatives, student representatives, parents in school associations)</li>
      <li>In-group identifications (e.g. religious identity) and setting-related identifications (e.g. shared school or urban identities) will be measured through scales of collective identity.</li>
    </ul>
